    "Next, unexplainable outcomes in machine learning refers to situations where the model's predictions need more justification [58].",
    "It makes it difficult for humans to understand how and why the model arrived at a particular decision [48,50,52,57].Moreover, contrastive fairness aims to ensure fairness in decisions by comparing outcomes for similar individuals who differ only in a protected attribute (such as race or gender)."
